main event: On March 17, 1961, two bright irregular objects with flashing lights were sighted south of Minden, Nevada, remaining stationary before exploding at the horizon.
interesting points: The sighting lasted from 2 to 4 minutes., The objects emitted bright flashes upon impact at the horizon., The report suggests the objects were not falling stars., The absence of other witnesses led to categorizing the data as insufficient., The objects' origin was uncertain, potentially manmade or transient.
sighted object: two bright irregular objects with flashing lights
witness description: The observed was driving south on Highway 95 when the sighting occurred.
